# gh-repo1 testing manually
name: Node.js CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    strategy:
      matrix:
        node-version: [12, 14, 16]   # Runs tests on these node versions

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v2
      
      - name: Use Node.js ${{ matrix.node-version }}
        uses: actions/setup-node@v2
        with:
          node-version: ${{ matrix.node-version }}
      
      - run: npm install
      - run: npm test
This workflow triggers on pushes and pull requests to the main branch, and it will run the CI build across Node.js versions 12, 14, and 16. You can customize it further based on your project's needs.











